high.mackenzie.autumn.lang.compiler.typesystem

Class CustomAnnotation

  • java.lang.Object
    • high.mackenzie.autumn.lang.compiler.typesystem.CustomAnnotation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IAnnotation

    public final class CustomAnnotation
extends java.lang.Object
implements IAnnotation
    An instance of this class represents an annotation instantiation.

    Example: @Person
    "Person" is the name of the annotation type (i.e. the annotation-definition).

    • Method Detail

      • getAnnotationType

        public IAnnotationType getAnnotationType()
        This method returns the type of the annotation-definition.

        This method may return null, under abnormal circumstances.
        For example, this method will return null, if the name of the annotation is misspelled.

        Specified by:
        getAnnotationType in interface IAnnotation
        Returns:
        the annotation-definition of the underlying annotation, or null, if no such object can be found.

      • getAnnotationValues

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getAnnotationValues()
        This method retrieves the values stored in the annotation, if it has any values.

        In terms of Java based code, the values are stored in an annotation-element named "value". The return-type of the element must be String[]. If no such element exists, then the annotation does not have any values. The default value of the "value" annotation-element is null.

        Specified by:
        getAnnotationValues in interface IAnnotation
        Returns:
        the value in the annotation.
